'''Paul Connett''' is a prominent [[Water fluoridation controversy|water fluoridation critic]],<ref name="Freeze">{{cite book|last1=Freeze|first1=R. Allan|last2=Lehr|first2=Jay H.|title=The Fluoride Wars: How a Modest Public Health Measure Became America's Longest Running Political Melodrama|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=9780470463673|pages=50–51|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Abh47vD7JTEC&pg=PA13&dq=%22fluoride+action+network%22&hl=en&sa=X&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22fluoride%20action%20network%22&f=false|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Consumer Health Digest #13-15|url=http://www.ncahf.org/digest13/13-15.html|publisher=[[The National Council Against Health Fraud]]|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Paul Connett|url=http://www.psr.org/chapters/oregon/paul-connett.html|publisher=[[Physicians for Social Responsibility]]|accessdate=7 November 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006101246/http://www.psr.org/chapters/oregon/paul-connett.html|archivedate=6 October 2014|df=}}</ref> executive director of the [[Binghamton, New York]] based ''Fluoride Action Network'' (FAN),<ref>{{cite web|title=Chemical & Engineering News: Government & Policy- Fluoride Risks Are Still A Challenge|url=https://pubs.acs.org/cen/government/84/8436gov1.html|website=[[Chemical & Engineering News]]|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Daley|first1=John|title=Denver Fluoride Fight Pits Activists Against Long-Standing Health Policy|url=http://www.cpr.org/news/story/denver-fluoride-fight-pits-activists-against-long-standing-health-policy|accessdate=7 May 2017|work=[[Colorado Public Radio]]|language=en}}</ref> one of the largest organizations opposing water fluoridation worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Fluoride Dialogue: CDHA Position Statements|url=http://www.cdha.ca/pdfs/Profession/Resources/ProbeFluoride.pdf|publisher=[[Canadian Dental Hygienists Association]]|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Morgan|first1=Matt|title=Wellington mulls re-adding Fluoride to water, sparking debate|url=http://www.mypalmbeachpost.com/news/news/local/wellingtons-water-the-debate-over-fluoride-use-sur/nrXcL/|accessdate=7 November 2016|publisher=[[Palm Beach Post]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Fluoride’s return in Wilkesboro sought|url=http://www.journalpatriot.com/news/fluoride-s-return-in-wilkesboro-sought/article_d788ef88-8992-11e6-9596-f734dd9ef6f7.html?mode=jqm|accessdate=7 November 2016|publisher=[[Wilkes Journal-Patriot]]}}</ref> Connett has been invited by environmental organizations opposing fluoridation to come and lecture on the subject in fluoridating countries such as [[Canada]], [[Israel]], [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Whiteman|first1=Ken|title=Stop fluoridation, London audience told|url=http://digitaljournal.com/article/304245|accessdate=7 May 2017|publisher=Digital Journal|date=3 March 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=תחקיר: מה עושה פלואוריד מסוכן במים שלנו?|url=http://ynet.co.il/Articles/3445244|accessdate=7 November 2016|publisher=[[Ynet]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Field|first1=Tony|title=Anti-fluoride campaigner opens debate in Auckland|url=http://www.newshub.co.nz/nznews/antifluoride-campaigner-opens-debate-in-auckland-2014020216|accessdate=7 November 2016|work=[[Newshub]]|date=2 February 2014}}</ref><ref name=Hansen>{{cite news|last1=Hansen|first1=Jane|title=Scare tactics: How anti-fluoride activists push their fear mongering on local councils|url=http://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/news/nsw/scare-tactics-how-antifluoride-activists-push-their-fear-mongering-on-local-councils/news-story/4901f6ce3246a8448d897102c2010c64|accessdate=7 May 2017|publisher=[[The Sunday Telegraph (Sydney)]]|date=6 September 2015}}</ref> Connett has stated "It’s politics that is interfering with science in this issue...It’s a matter of political will, and you cannot change political will if you don’t get the people. We must involve the people."<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mercola|first1=Dr Joseph|title=The Health Hazards of Water Fluoridation (VIDEO)|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/dr-mercola/warning-this-daily-habit-_b_741635.html|accessdate=7 May 2017|work=[[Huffington Post]]|date=11 October 2010}}</ref>
Connett is a graduate of [[Cambridge University]]. He holds a Ph.D. in chemistry from [[Dartmouth College]]. After teaching chemistry and toxicology for 23 years at [[St. Lawrence University]], [[Canton, NY]], he retired from his full professorship. He is currently also the director of the ''American Environmental Health Studies Project'' (AEHSP).<ref>[http://www.americanhealthstudies.org/connett.bio.html Paul Connett bio]</ref><ref>[http://www.chelseagreen.com/authors/paul_connett/ Paul Connett and AESHP]</ref>
In 2004, Connett published the paper ''50 Reasons to Oppose Fluoridation''.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Connett|first1=Paul H.|title=Fifty reasons to oppose fluoridation|journal=Medical Veritas: The Journal of Medical Truth|date=April 2004|volume=1|issue=1|pages=70–80|doi=10.1588/medver.2004.01.00014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Fluoridation questions and answers|url=http://www.health.govt.nz/our-work/preventative-health-wellness/fluoridation/fluoridation-questions-and-answers|website=[[Ministry of Health (New Zealand)]]|accessdate=7 November 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Fight over fluoride reignited|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/9650579/Fight-over-fluoride-reignited|accessdate=7 November 2016|work=[[Stuff.co.nz]]|date=26 January 2014|language=English}}</ref> In 2010 he coauthored; ''The Case against Fluoride: How Hazardous Waste Ended Up in Our Drinking Water and the Bad Science and Powerful Politics That Keep It There'' along with Dr. James Beck and Dr. H. Spedding Micklem.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Peckham|first1=Stephen|title=The case against fluoride: how hazardous waste ended up in our drinking water and the bad science and powerful politics that keep it there, by Paul Connett, James Beck, and H Spedding Micklem|journal=[[Critical Public Health]]|date=March 2012|volume=22|issue=1|pages=113–114|doi=10.1080/09581596.2011.593350}}</ref> He also wrote the book in 2013; "The Zero Waste Solution".<ref>[http://zwia.org/aboutus/zwia-history/ Paul Connett and ZWIA]</ref> and assisted the city of [[Naples]] in pursuing its zero waste strategy.<ref>[http://www.zerowasteeurope.eu/tag/paul-connett/ Paul Connett helping Naples]</ref>
